The paper deals with the problem of managing interference and ensuring secrecy in a communication channel, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper focuses on the security aspect of the communication, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also proposes achievable schemes and outer bounds, which involve coding and transmission techniques, making it relevant to the networking and internet architecture sub-category (cs.NI). The paper also deals with the partitioning of encoded messages and the careful selection of side information, which are techniques used in source coding and data compression (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a combination of Marton's coding scheme and stochastic encoding, which is a technique used in multimedia systems (cs.MM).
